'''''Lock Charmer''''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]]: ''El cerrajero'') is a 2014  Argentine [[drama film]] written and directed by [[Natalia Smirnoff]].<ref>{{cite web |title=LatinoBuzz: Natalia Smirnoff Director of 'Lock Charmer' On Premiering Her Film at Sundance 2014|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/sydneylevine/latinobuzz-natalia-smirnoff-director-of-lock-charmer-on-premiering-her-film-at-sundance-2014|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sundance 2014: Meet Natalia Smirnoff, Argentine Director of ‘Lock Charmer’ and Lover of ‘The Avengers’|url=http://www.remezcla.com/2014/latin/sundance-2014-meet-natalia-smirnoff-argentine-director-of-lock-charmer-and-lover-of-the-avengers/|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Natalia Smirnoff, Lock Charmer|url=http://www.screendaily.com/features/natalia-smirnoff-lock-charmer/5065084.article|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref> The film premiered in-competition in the ''World Cinema Dramatic Competition'' at [[2014 Sundance Film Festival]] on January 21, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sundance 2014: World Cinema Dramatic Competition|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/sundance-2014-world-cinema-dramatic-competition|accessdate=January 18, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Lock Charmer (El cerrajero) - Director Natalia Smirnoff|url=http://filmmakermagazine.com/83022-lock-charmer-el-cerrajero-director-natalia-smirnoff/#.U11H3FWSykc|accessdate=January 18, 2014}}</ref>

The film later premiered at the 2014 [[Fribourg International Film Festival]] on March 29, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lock Charmer - El Cerrajero |url=http://www.fiff.ch/programme-2014/films/competition-internationale-longs-metrages/lock-charmer-el-cerrajero.html|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=28e FESTIVAL INTERNATIONAL DE FILMS DE FRIBOURG 2014 - March 29 - April 5, 2014|url=http://www.gep.de/interfilm/englisch/interfilm3850_28520.htm|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref> 

==Plot==
Thirty-three-year-old locksmith, Sebastian doesn't believe in committed relationships. He learns from his recent girlfriend, Monica, that she's pregnant but she isn't sure that he is the father. During the same time, he discovers that whenever he fixes someones locks, he gets a vision into their lives, which reveals their feelings. Soon this power starts to complicate his life. After he warns a maid named Daisy that her boyfriend is stealing from her boss, she leaves her boyfriend, and Sebastian takes her in. But when he sees a vision about his own life, Sebastian is forced to examine every aspect of his life.

